 _AN-CBLA2AF0FT 920212 FT 12 FEB 92 / Commodities and Agriculture: 'Mad cow' disease spreads to antelopes By DAVID OWEN THE CONDITION known in cattle as 'mad cow disease', spongiform encephalopathies, has been found in Britain's sparsely-scattered antelope population, the government has admitted.
 The statistics - released in response to a written question from Mr Ron Davies, a Labour agriculture spokesman - show a disconcertingly rapid increase in the number of sheep found to have the disease.
